'''OAT'''s ('''Obligations assimilables du Trésor''') are [[government bonds]] issued by Agence France Trésor (French Treasury), generally by auction according to an annual calendar published in advance. These [[fungible]] [[securities]] are issued with [[Maturity (finance)|maturities]] of seven to 50 years, and have become the method of choice for placing the French government’s long-term debt.<ref>[http://www.aft.gouv.fr/aft_en_21/debt_management_51/products_248/oats_252/oats_623.html Agence France Trésor]</ref>

